{
  "texts": [
    "We installed a ROS2-based environment in the normal world.To evaluate the cost of sanitizing video feeds, we consider the setup shown in Figure 6.",
    "We built a pair of ROS2 applications, the first of which publishes a video feed that the second consumes directly, as shown in Figure 6 a.",
    "This is our baseline, which we run with a workload in which the publisher sends a video feed consisting of 250 frames (resolution 320×240 pixels, at 30 frames/second).",
    "The publisher converts each frame into ROS2's message format, which the subscriber receives and converts back to a video frame.",
    "We then implemented redirection and sanitization of the video feed as shown in Figure 6 b, in which Sanitizer-FE exclusively subscribes to the feed of the publisher, and redirects the flow to a trusted sanitizer in the secure world."
  ]
}